description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an Acute or Emergency Nurse looking for a new challenge and to work in a brand new purpose built Emergency Assessment Centre? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are challenging the traditional flow of patients through the system by finding new ways of working and thinking outside of the box to give inpatient treatment on an outpatient basis. So if you are looking for a challenge and a way to improve patient journeys as well as develop new skills and experiences this may be the post for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ambulatory Emergency Care has been open since 2014 at Wexham Park Hospital and aims to provide rapid assessment and decision making, urgent investigations and treatment to avoid unnecessary admissions and improve the patient pathway. We work closely with the Emergency Department as well as many other specialist teams and since the unit opened we have seen over 40,000 patients and avoided unnecessary admissions for over 90% of them. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are now settled in our brand new &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;unit which has 20 assessment cubicles as well as 10 treatment chairs as part of a £49million new Emergency Assessment Centre which opened in Spring 2019. We are becoming busier and busier each month as we grow and now see over 1000 patients a month as well as developing fast-track access for the Emergency Department and Ambulance Service to be a 2nd front-door to the hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; We are looking for a talented individual to join our team to enable us to continue the exciting journey as we continue to expand our service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; service runs on long day shifts of 09:00-22:00 Monday-Friday and 09:00-21:00 at weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Further Details please contact Claire Gargini - AEC Unit Manager at c.gargini@nhs.net or Sean Harding - Consultant Nurse Acute Care on s.harding@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
